{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3307","heading":"Defenses, liability, and protection of trans­feree","label":"3307 Defenses, liability, and protection of trans­feree","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/ptVI/ch176/schD","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective 180 days after , and applicable with respect to certain actions for debts owed the United States pending in court on that effective date, see , set out as a note under .Nov. 29, 1990section 3631 of Pub. L. 101–647section 3001 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Good Faith Transfer","label":"a .—Good Faith Transfer","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A transfer or obligation is not voidable under section 3304(b) with respect to a person who took in good faith and for a reasonably equivalent value or against any transferee or obligee subsequent to such person.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Limitation","label":"b .—Limitation","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the first transferee of the asset or the person for whose benefit the transfer was made; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any subsequent transferee, other than a good faith transferee who took for value or any subsequent transferee of such good-faith transferee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Value of Asset","label":"c .—Value of Asset","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For purposes of subsection (b), the value of the asset is the value of the asset at the time of the transfer, subject to adjustment as the equities may require.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Rights of Good Faith Transferees and Obligees","label":"d .—Rights of Good Faith Transferees and Obligees","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a lien on or a right to retain any interest in the asset transferred;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"enforcement of any obligation incurred; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a reduction in the amount of the liability on the judgment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Exceptions","label":"e .—Exceptions","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"termination of a lease upon default by the debtor when the termination is pursuant to the lease and applicable law; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"enforcement of a security interest in compliance with article 9 of the Uniform Commercial Code or its equivalent in effect in the State where the property is located.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":".—Limitation of Voidability","label":"f .—Limitation of Voidability","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to the extent the insider gives new value to or for the benefit of the debtor after the transfer is made unless the new value is secured by a valid lien;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if made in the ordinary course of business or financial affairs of the debtor and the insider; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/f/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3307/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3307%2Ff%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if made pursuant to a good-faith effort to rehabilitate the debtor and the transfer secured both present value given for that purpose and an antecedent debt of the debtor.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
